MBOMBELA – Three suspects held up the staff at Romans Pizza at Sonpark Centre last night.  Police spokesman, Capt Dawie Pretorius said the men entered the shop just before closing time at around 20:30. “No customers were in the store at the time.  The one suspect wore a balaklava while the other two did not conceal their faces.  They held them up with handguns and took all the float cash that was left in the till.” About R2800 was stolen, and nobody was injured during the robbery. The men fled in a white Nissan Almeira. Police are still busy with the investigation. Lowvelder will update with more information as it becomes available.